# Node.js Security Guidelines

Applied when working with Node.js service code. Australian English spelling throughout.

---

## Child Process Safety

- Use `execFile` (not `exec`) — it does not invoke a shell, eliminating shell injection
- Never interpolate user-controlled data into command strings
- Validate file paths before passing to child processes; reject paths containing `..` or null bytes
- Set an execution timeout on all child processes; terminate on timeout

---

## SSRF Prevention

- Validate all user-supplied URLs against an explicit allowlist of permitted hostnames before making outbound HTTP requests
- Block requests to loopback (`127.x.x.x`, `::1`, `localhost`) and RFC 1918 private ranges
- Use a dedicated HTTP client with configurable redirect limits; disable open redirects for internal clients

---

## HTTP Security Headers

- Apply `helmet()` middleware to every Express/Fastify app; configure CSP explicitly
- Set a strict body size limit (`express.json({ limit: '100kb' })`) to prevent memory exhaustion
- Enable `HSTS` in production; enforce HTTPS at the load balancer and in the app

---

## Rate Limiting and Abuse Prevention

- Apply rate limiting to all public-facing endpoints; use stricter limits on auth endpoints
- Use `express-rate-limit` or Fastify equivalents; back with Redis for distributed deployments
- Return `429 Too Many Requests` with a `Retry-After` header

---

## Secrets and Environment

- Validate all required environment variables at startup with Zod; fail fast on missing secrets
- Never log secrets, tokens, or password fields; configure Pino `redact` for sensitive paths
- Use a secrets manager (AWS Secrets Manager, Vault, Doppler) in production — not `.env` files

---

## Dependency Security

- Run `npm audit --audit-level=high` in CI as a blocking step
- Use `npm ci` in CI for reproducible installs
- Review and pin critical dependency versions; use Dependabot or Renovate for automated updates
- Regularly remove unused packages (`npx depcheck`)

---

## Checklist

- [ ] `execFile` used for all child processes; no user input in command strings
- [ ] Outbound HTTP requests to user-supplied URLs validated against an allowlist
- [ ] `helmet()` applied; CSP configured; body size limited
- [ ] Rate limiting on public and auth endpoints
- [ ] `npm audit --audit-level=high` passes in CI
- [ ] Secrets validated at startup; never logged or committed
- [ ] Stack traces not returned in API responses (`NODE_ENV=production`)
